      "id": "1088319247920398377",
      "type": "Default",
      "timestamp": "2023-03-23T13:32:08.698+09:00",
      "timestampEdited": null,
      "callEndedTimestamp": null,
      "isPinned": false,
      "content": "Really not much to say here. You don't have a decision to make at this event, you just enter and get the reward. Both rewards are excellent, 100 souls being particularly nice for an early red/green key break. Removing strikes is pretty much always something you are very happy to do, just improving the quality of your draws generally. My biggest takeaway is that the events in downfall are on average much more rewarding than the events in standard mode, and thus you should probably lean slightly more towards question marks than hallway fights in downfall. There are a shockingly large number of events that can give you 100 souls, probably to help with key breaking. Less events involve health loss as well if I'm not mistaken. There are also several very strong character specific events, like grim forge and gem mine for guardian.",
