      "type": "Default",
      "timestamp": "2023-03-23T15:21:19.956+09:00",
      "timestampEdited": null,
      "callEndedTimestamp": null,
      "isPinned": false,
      "content": "The events where you can fight to get all/more/better rewards (lady in blue, wheel of change, augmentor, living wall, possibly more) are probably the most egregious balance problem with downfall. They really stand as being far too easy compared to how much stuff you get for fighting them. Part of the problem is that they don't scale appropriately with the act you're in (lady in blue and wheel of change), which means that they are way too easy if you run into them in late act 2 or act 3. Events in standard mode have a much more balanced set of risks and rewards associated with them",
      "author": {
