    {
      "id": "1088518491465859082",
      "type": "Default",
      "timestamp": "2023-03-24T02:43:52.061+09:00",
      "timestampEdited": null,
      "callEndedTimestamp": null,
      "isPinned": false,
      "content": "To be completely fair, I do think that A20 heart runs are a little bit too difficult/frustrating in standard mode, so I don't mind downfall changing things to be a little easier in places. Some of the events are just too generous, or don't involve interesting enough decision making because of how strong one of the options is. There is a point of balance between events that are too nasty (forgotten altar, sssserpent) and events that are too easy (lady in blue, wheel of change). I think the right balance for an event is somewhere around old beggar/pleading vagrant/bonfire spirits/living wall base game version. About 1 card remove/transform/upgrade for around 75 gold. Scrap ooze and shining light are also pretty well designed in my opinion, trading 10-15 health for a relic/upgrades, and you can decide whether that risk is worth it based on current health/deck strength/difficulty of current path.",
